result.execSummary:
The defendant Frank Edward Colon-Springhoff was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Knowingly Violate a Domestic Abuse Order - Injunction [Modifiers: Domestic Abuse Assessments], an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 813.12(8)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Frank Edward Colon-Springhoff in court with attorney Gregory A. Renden.  Porchia Sharese Lewand appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  AS to the charged offense:    Defendant was advised of constitutional rights and maximum penalties, and further advised that if not a United States citizen deportation is possible. Defendant examined as to plea, and entered a plea of guilty.  Court found defendant freely, voluntarily and intelligently waived all constitutional rights. Plea questionnaire waiver of rights and addendum to plea questionnaire received and filed. Parties stipulated to the criminal complaint as factual basis to sustain defendant's plea. Court found defendant guilty as charged in the complaint and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered into the record.  
Sentencing proceeded.  Statements to the court by parties.  Additional statement by Maggie B. via interpreter Alberto Aguilar who is sworn to interpret.
Court sentences the defendant to serve 1 day House of Correction with credit for 1 day TIME SERVED.  The court orders defendant to pay ALL costs, fees, assessments and surcharges and to provide DNA sample and pay surcharge by 2-29-2016 or a civil judgment shall be entered.
